cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper deals with saliency methods for deep neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method for integrating saliency scores, which involves optimization and considers joint activation patterns of pixels, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the issue of adversarial attacks, which are a common concern in computer security, suggesting that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) may also be a relevant category. Finally, the paper includes theoretical analysis, indicating a potential fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
